<br>
I was fighting in HH Pass last night with a small group.  We were the only group fighting Orcs so no competition.  Well, no competition means things can get a little out of hand every once in awhile.  We take down half a train and see 3 more orcs joining the fight, so I call for everyone to zone.<br>
<br>
I land one more backstab to get a mercenary off our cleric and head for the zone.  I see my health dropping steadily and it's nearly gone when I get to the zone.  Unfortunately I took one more hit and got knocked unconscious... Fortunately I fell into the zone.  After what seemed like an eternity I finished zoning to the welcome message of:<br>
<br>
&quot;Player is beneath world, moving to a safe location&quot;.  Safe location is subjective, I guess, but I landed about a 30 second run from the zone to Rivervale.  In Kithcor.  At night.  So I have 11 hitpoints, and all my buffs somehow disappeared even though I didn't die.  I make it to the rivervale zone and start bandaging myself...<br>
<br>
So my closest?  Knocked unconscious, fell into zone, woke up with a few hitpoints left in a high level undead-controlled zone (:<br>
<br>
