Many of you might have heard something about me, the crazy Darkie who decided to get a Burning Rapier before he gets a last name.  The quest ineveitably brings me to Blackborrow.  And ineveitably I learn to hate the brewers, but being there does allow me to make plenty of jokes about the bad smell coming from the Barbarians.  Anyway, sitting there and waiting for a brewer to show up is boring, so I run into the commander room and kill him every few minutes, and then run up to the ledge above it and kill all the gnolls there.  One time after a particularly brutal fight with the commander I ran into three Elite Guardsmen up on the ridge.  No chance to back down so I fight.  One goes down, I am severly wounded.  Another falls and the thrid pounds me hard.  Then out of no where his eyes go wide as a blue aura surrounds me and heals all my wounds.  This one is not very brave and runs near the end of the fight and I promptly kill him in one swipe.  Out of nowhere I am hit in the back of the head.  Somehow another Elite made it up there and he hit me hard.  Down he goes and yet another arrives.  I am hurting and almost dead, victory in the vile things eyes when yet again a blue aura surrounds me.  I don't even give this one a chance to run.  I turn around to find my benefactor and I see a... WOLF!  I bow low to him, wondering why he would help my dark kind out and he speaks the words, &quot;Houma, I have heard of your goodness and this valient quest you are on.  I have helped but a little and only a little more can I do. Here.&quot; and I feel much much faster.  After riffleing through the fur of the unfortunates I through them into the water, keeping one of their skins.  I run down for my rendevous with the Brewer and he has the tenacity to jump on me!  Promptly he is killed, and alas, still no cask.<br>
<br>
Later that evening I was awaiting the arrival of the Master Brewer, having sent all of his underlings to the Abyss, when I hear a someones voice yelling &quot;TRAIN!&quot;  Knowing that they mean that a whole bunch of the ugly things were following them outside I promptly get into a corner and hide.  Watching them go past I wait for the gnoll commander and pick him out.  Low and behold another commander attacks me at the same time.  I slay both and sit down to rest.  I am feeling good about myself when an elite walks by and myself never passing up an opportunity I jump out of the shadows and place a nice hole in his backside.  Little did I know that this was the lead of the &quot;train&quot; that upon having lost both their commanders had decided to return to their posts.  Two of his companions joined him and the rest of the vile gnolls decided to cheer their comrades on.  I dropped the one and ran.  Near the entrance, never being one to back down from a fight I turn and dispatch andother Elite.  As the last one comes in, the smaller prey had fled away from me.  Praying to  Bristlebane to guide me in the hereafter I stab one last time and do a backflip.  Being the smart one I am I heard the gnoll fall but also I heard my own body hit the ground snf move half an inch backwards.  Then from the gods these words appear in my mind &quot;LOADING, PLEASE WAIT.&quot;  I have often noticed this in passing between territories and had just happened to be in the right place at the right time I guess.<br>
<br>
OOC: Both true though the druid had played another character I had helped out, he didn't say all that.  It was late at night when only about fifteen people were actually there.  And no... I still have not gotten my cask yet... stupid spawn rates.<br>
<br>
Houma, Rogue of the 16th Stab<br>
