lf.<br>
<br>
Another was in MM, some guy was fighting an enchanter in the tower thing I believe. I saw a 21 rogue backstab the guy while he was fighting. I was thinking, dueling at that place? Huh? Something or other begins to cast a spell. You are stunned! I was sitting down hidden waiting for full hp to take out an initiate. I was at 4 bubbles, get hit down to 2 bubbles in a few seconds, I'm charmed! I'm running around chasing some guy trying to stab him. Finally he zones, and I'm near the tunnel heading to the graveyard. I was thinking, okay once this charm breaks I've gotta be ready. Wait for a long while, charm breaks, I'm spinning in circles, get hit down to half a bubble while I am, speed strafe the heck to zone. I take the shortcut over the hill, I'm just barely running. 5 feet from zone, hit by more mobs, down to a sliver of health, zone.... into the middle of Lfay.<br>
<br>
Then later, I was fully buffed with symbols, bravery, and holy armor. A cleric, mage, and I were the only ones in zone. There was only one way to break a spawn (because of the darn pathing grr) So I pull a pledge, along with a garg, a caster, and an initiate joined in a repop. Big battle ensues. Bring down the caster real quick. Couldn't get off one spell.... ow darn damage shields. Garg goes down... then the pledge is next... cleric is OOM, I'm down to a bubble and a half. I tell the others to zone, and then I follow, get hit down to a sliver of health, zone. Into LFay at the MM entrance, only this time with no buffs.<br>
<br>
One lesson I learned, zoning when near death or dead is a very interesting experience and good for laughs a lot of the time.<br>
 <br>
You are not prey until a predator knows of your existence (and even then the roles may be switched)<br>
