ouse tradition!<br>
So....<br>
I was playing my girlfriends Barb Warrior the other night... she's level 12. I'm fighting in Blackburrow... and the only things I really fear are commanders and high elites. <br>
Random lowbie shouts &quot;TRAIN to zone!&quot;<br>
I'm near the bridge so I decide to stick around before beating a retreat. I see the aforementioned &quot;person of lower levels&quot; running from a group of like... a gnoll guardsmen and a coupla regular gnolls.<br>
&quot;Dang newbies,&quot; I scoff to myself, &quot;Thats not a REAL train.&quot;<br>
Wade into battle with my Shiny Brass Halberd swinging... then notice that the REAL train is the 2 elites, commander, and 3 guardsmen following a bit behind. I yelp somewhat loudly and quite unlike a warrior.<br>
I bellow my usual &quot;TRAIN TO ZONE... MOVE IT OR LOSE IT!!!&quot; a few times to warn everyone and then start my ascent to zone. I get out the top door... and get stunned BAD... 40hp to go... make it close to zone... 10hp... get stunned. *SMACK*<br>
Fall unconscious.<br>
Regain consciousness... and make it to zone... with ONE hitpoint. Meanwhile I'm praying to the Tribunal that I don't get smacked hard while zoning.<br>
Make it to the other side... fall unconscious... again.<br>
Pop up... and sit down. Chuckling to myself about &quot;Who's the newbie again?&quot;<br>
<br>
Kasugai<br>
